post_text:
FOR FAMILIES WHO DID NOT APPLY THE FIRST TIME!

Louisiana is reopening the Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) program for families who did not apply in May and June. Families of children who receive free or reduced-price school meals may be eligible to receive financial benefits for meals missed in 2019-2020 when schools closed due to the pandemic. Apply from September 8 at 8 a.m. to September 29 at 5 p.m. These one-time benefits total $285 per child. Parents who applied for free meals in May will receive $91.20 per eligible child. The online application is simple. The information submitted must exactly match the information on file with the school system in order for the application to successfully submit. #louisianabelieves

https://pebt.doe.louisiana.gov/PublicApps/SNP/offline

Iberville Parish School District
July 24 at 9:05 AM ·

CareSouth Medical and Dental along with other community sponsors is hosting a COVID-19 Drive-thru Community Testing and Back to School Giveaway in Plaquemine on July 28 and Donaldsonville on July 29.

The event will take place from 9 a.m. to noon. CareSouth will be distributing 300 backpacks filled with school supplies and our community partners will also be distributing items. Supplies will be given on a first-come, first-serve basis.

Parents have to be tested to get the supplies and children must be present. Parents are also encouraged to get their kids ages 12 and up tested as well. You must pre-register to take the test at caresouth.org.

In partnership with the Three O'Clock Project, free grab-and-go breakfast and lunch, for all kids of Iberville Parish, 18 and under will begin tomorrow, Wednesday, April 8, 2020 through Wednesday, April 29, 2020.

Wednesday, April 8, 2020, you will receive breakfast & lunch for Wednesday, Thursday and Friday.

Breakfast and lunch for multiple days will be provided on Monday's & Wednesday's. Meals will include storage and heating instructions.

Guardian may pick up meals on behalf of children.

Meals will be distributed at White Castle High School, MSA West Academy, Iberville Elementary, North Iberville and East Iberville.

post_text:
Special COVID-19 Blanket Employment Certificates for Minors to work in Louisiana

The Louisiana Workforce Commission (LWC) will begin issuing sixty (60) day blanket Employment Certificates for employers desiring to employ minors in the State of Louisiana. Employment Certificates issued due to this event shall expire sixty (60) days from the date of issuance. Upon expiration, employers will be required to obtain Employment Certificates as required pursuant to La. R.S. 23:181 et. seq.

After 60 day expiration:

Employers desiring to obtain an Employment Certificate pursuant to this memorandum must submit a completed and signed “Application to Employ Minors under 18” along with proof of age to laborprograms@lwc.la.gov. The application can be downloaded from the Louisiana Workforce Commission’s website or at the following link: http://www.laworks.net/downloads/WFD/MinorApplicationToEmployForm.pdf.

post_text: Per Governor John Bel Edwards, all public schools, including Iberville Parish Public School System, will be closed beginning Monday, March 16th through Monday, April 13th. Spring Break will continue as planned. At this time, students are expected to return to school Monday, April 20th. Beginning Monday, March 16th, all athletic events have been canceled until further notice. Please continue to follow social media, the District’s web page, and your local news station for additional information.
text: Per Governor John Bel Edwards, all public schools, including Iberville Parish Public School System, will be closed beginning Monday, March 16th through Monday, April 13th. Spring Break will continue as planned. At this time, students are expected to return to school Monday, April 20th. Beginning Monday, March 16th, all athletic events have been canceled until further notice. Please continue to follow social media, the District’s web page, and your local news station for additional information.

post_text: At their regular board meeting, IPSB recognized Exxon Mobil, along with the help of Exxon employee, Mr. M. Smith and St. Gabriel Councilman, J. Hayes for donating $10,000 that will be divided between East Iberville and MSA East Pre-K Programs. The money will be used to support STEM activities and field trips that spark interest in science, technology, engineering and math. #IPSBproud #ActforImpact

post_text:
The Louisiana Construction Education Foundation (LCEF) Jump Start Construction Connect Scholars Program is now accepting applications for a $1,000 scholarship. The scholarship is geared toward students who have earned the Jump Start Diploma, earned a National Center for Construction Education and Research (NCCER) credential, and are or will be enrolled in an LCTCS campus on a construction pathway or in an Associated Builders and Contractors training program.

This is the state’s first and only scholarship dedicated exclusively to Jump Start graduates. This effort is a collaboration of the Louisiana Construction Education Foundation, Louisiana Community and Technical College System, and the Department.

Apply here: https://www.louisianabelieves.com/docs/default-source/jumpstart/jump-start-construction-connect-scholars-program-application.pdf?sfvrsn=33459a1f_4
